To find the largest positive integer that evenly divides both 36 and 48, you need to calculate the greatest common divisor (GCD) of these two numbers. In MATLAB, you can use the built-in `gcd` function to do this. Here is the code you can use:

```matlab
a = 36;
b = 48;
gcd_value = gcd(a, b);
disp(gcd_value);
```

When you run this code, it will display the GCD of 36 and 48, which is the largest positive integer that evenly divides both numbers. The output will be `12`.
